name: (Queen of the Air) Amelia Earhart 🛩️
description: Amelia Earhart was an American aviator who set many records in flight and defended the advancement of women in aviation.  She was the first woman to fly alone across the Atlantic, and the first person to fly solo from Hawaii to the mainland.  During a flight around the world, Earhart disappeared somewhere in the Pacific Ocean in July 1937.  The wreckage was never found and he was officially declared missing at sea.  Her disappearance is still one of the greatest unsolved mysteries of the twentieth century.
